GoodNet — Licensing
====================

The platform consists of the kernel and the SDK. They live under a single
license model. Plugins are independent builds against the SDK and carry
their own licenses; each plugin directory has its own LICENSE file.


Platform Components
-------------------

  Kernel  (core/)                    GNU General Public License v2.0 (GPL-2.0)
                                     →  core/LICENSE

  SDK     (sdk/, public headers)     MIT License
                                     →  sdk/LICENSE


Plugins
-------

Plugins are independent builds. Each is licensed at the discretion of its
authors. Common cases:

  - Open MIT plugins ship with the upstream tree under plugins/ as a
    convenience for development; they remain independently licensed.
  - Closed-source or commercial plugins live in their own repositories
    and link against the installed SDK.

Loading a plugin at runtime through the stable C ABI does NOT trigger
GPL copyleft on the kernel side: the boundary between kernel and plugin
is the SDK, which is MIT and explicitly intended for cross-license use.

To discover the license of a specific plugin, consult its own LICENSE file.


Copyright (c) 2026 GoodNet contributors (kernel + SDK).
Plugins copyright their respective authors.
